@node introduction "RxTD Guide - Introduction"

    RxTD is a set of Arexx scripts that converts ToolsDaemon prefs file into an Arexx
  script to add the menus to os3.9 in a system legal way.

    As a new legal version of a ToolsDaemon-type util (with pretty prefs:)) is being
  worked on I don`t think this collection of scripts will be developed much b4 they
  are replaced by an all in one solution.

@endnode

@node requirements "RxTD Guide - Requirements"

  · WB3.9

  · WBRun (Included with Stephan Rupprecht's permission)

  · A setup Rexxmast - @{"Quick Guide" link requirementsrexxmast}

  · A ToolsDaemon prefs file

  @{B}OPTIONAL@{UB}

  · TDPrefs2 Doesn`t complain if you press save without ToolsDaemon running

@endnode

@node requirementsrexxmast "RxTD Guide - Requirements - Setting up Rexxmast"

Two ways to get RexxMast to be run every time you reboot

  @{B}Automatically@{UB}
  This doesn't work if this guide has been taken out of it's original drawer.

  @{"Click" RX "CheckRexxMast.rexx"} here, If you don't get a requester @{"Click" System "Echo >>S:User-Startup Run >NIL: Sys:System/RexxMast"} here to add RexxMast to
  S:User-startup.

@{B}or@{UB}

  @{B}Manually@{UB}
  Type 'Ed s:user-startup' at a command prompt (Press RAmiga+E on workbench)

  Look for a line containing Rexxmast.

  If you can`t find one add the line:
    Sys:System/RexxMast >NIL:

    to the end of the file.

  Press Esc then x and press return
    

@endnode

@node Installation "RxTD Guide - Installation"

  Double click the install icon to run the DOS script
    If versions of the libs, handlers or WBrun exist then they will not be copied
    in case it overwrites a newer version, I'll fix this when/if I create a proper
    installer install script.
  Copy the docs drawer whereever you want
@{B}or@{UB}
  copy the contents of the Rexx directory to rexx:
  type 'rx rexx:RxTDCreateMenu' at a command prompt
  * Check versions of existing files before copying...
    the contents of the libs directory to libs:
    the contents of the l directory to l:
    the contents of the c directory to c:
  double click on RxTDMenu in WBStartup
  Copy the docs drawer whereever you want

@{B}DONT FORGET@{UB} Remove toolsdaemon from WBStartup

@endnode

@node gettingstart "RxTD Guide - Getting started"

@endnode

@node usage "RxTD Guide - Usage"

    Install as per @{"instructions" link installation} and use the 'ToolsPrefs...' entry in the Tools menu
  to change the menus as you did with ToolsDaemon.

    The file Rexx:RxTDHandle has a prefs section so you can speed-up/simplify loading
  left-out files, just load it into your favourite text editor and change the setting.

    The file Rexx:RxTDCreateMenu has a prefs section so you can set the name&path of
  generated menu script, which stops WBStartup+ user ending up with 2 copies of the
  script. Just load the script into a text editor and change the setting.

@endnode

@node supportprogs "RxTD Guide - Support programs"

  WBRun   - @{B}By@{UB} Stephan Rupprecht
            Adds the ability to fool programs they were started from Workbench

            The original docs are included @{"WBStartEmu" link "WBStartEmu.doc/MAIN"}

  RxTDFix - @{B}By@{UB} John Nelson (me :))
            Fixes the quote problem, change all required [] in ToolsPrefs to
            `C:RxTDFix []` (Include the ` backticks NOTE ` NOT ')

            Click @{"`C:RxTDFix []`" SYSTEM "Copy Clipboard0 Clips:0"} to copy it to the clipboard then you can just press
            RightAmiga+V to paste into the command gadget in ToolsPrefs.

            @{"Source" link "RxTDFix.e/MAIN"} code is included in the docs drawer

  aslFReq - @{B}By@{UB} John Nelson
            Fixes the quote problem and brings up an asl filerequester if no file
            is selected. Replace [] with `aslFReq []` in ToolsPrefs for commands
            you want to add filerequesters to.

            Click @{"`aslFReq []`" SYSTEM "Copy Clipboard1 Clips:0"} to copy it to the clipboard then you can just press
            RightAmiga+V to paste into the command gadget in ToolsPrefs.

            @{"Source" link "aslFReq.e/MAIN"} code is included in the docs drawer

@endnode

@node problems "RxTD Guide - Problems"

@{B}Known with solutions@{UB}

  @{B}Problem@{UB}
    ToolsPrefs brings up a 'ToolsDaemon is not running' requester when Save is pressed.
  @{B}Solution@{UB}
    Download and use TDPrefs2 from aminet. Rename it 'ToolsPrefs' and place it in prefs.


@{B}Working on@{UB}

  Please report any bugs you find to @{"me" link author}.


@{B}Maybe later (hard to implement)@{UB}

    Some programs give 'File not found' or have problems with their tooltypes some
  of this caused by the way I'm adding quote marks around filenames. REMEMBER to only
  have [] in commands that you want to pass the currently selected file's names to

  Try the support program @{"RxTDFix" link supportprogs} to get around this.

@{B}No solution I can think of... (Ideas anyone?)@{UB}

    Running DOpus disables some of workbench's new features including the Arexx
  command used to add menu items.  If you run RxTDMenu before DOpus (in WBStartup)
  it`s not a problem unless you edit the menus in which case they can't be re-added

    The RxTDCreateMenu script runs automatically after the menus are changed
  to update the RxTDMenu script, please wait for disk activity to stop before
  accessing menus or it could corrupt the WBStartup/RxTDMenu script.


@endnode

